 ✅ Key Features

- 🔐 User Registration & Secure Login  
- 📝 Complaint Submission via Form  
- 📊 Real-Time Complaint Status Tracking  
- 💬 Chat Interface Between Users and Agents  
- 🛠 Admin Dashboard to Assign & Monitor Complaints  
- 👥 Role-Based Access: User, Agent, Admin  
- 🔐 Authentication using JWT  
- 🌐 RESTful API Integration

 🧠 Technologies Used

- *Frontend:* React.js, Material UI, Bootstrap, Axios  
- *Backend:* Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, Mongoose  
- *Authentication:* JSON Web Token (JWT)  
- *Communication:* Socket.IO (Real-time chat)

 ⚙ How to Run the Project Locally :

1️.Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/Mujasimshaik786/Complaint-registery.git

2️.Install Dependencies

 Frontend
cd complaint-registery/frontend
npm install

# Backend
cd ../backend
npm install

3️.Run the Application

 Backend
cd backend
npm start

Frontend (in a new terminal)
cd ../frontend
npm start

🌐 Frontend: http://localhost:3000
🌐 Backend: http://localhost:5000 (if configured properly)


